com.atlassian.jira.project.AbstractProjectManager#updateProject(Project updatedProject, String name, String description, String lead, String url, Long assigneeType, Long avatarId) receives the avatarId as the last parameter but then delegates to com.atlassian.jira.project.ProjectManager#updateProject by passing null instead of the avatarId that is passed in.

AbstractProjectManager#updateProject
{code}
// lines 425-428
public Project updateProject(Project updatedProject, String name, String description, String lead, String url, Long assigneeType, Long avatarId)
    {
        return updateProject(updatedProject, name, description, lead, url, assigneeType, null, null);
    }
{code}

should be 

{code}
public Project updateProject(Project updatedProject, String name, String description, String lead, String url, Long assigneeType, Long avatarId)
    {
        return updateProject(updatedProject, name, description, lead, url, assigneeType, avatarId, null);
    }
{code}

